text: hey folks! it’s transgender awareness week, a time set aside to help raise the visibility of transgender and gender non-conforming people, and to address the issues the community faces. there’s some good information around it on the glaad website here: <http://www.glaad.org/transweek>

attachments.title: Transgender Awareness Week #TransWeek
attachments.text: November 14 – 20 individuals and organizations around the country will participate in Transgender Awareness Week to help raise the visibility of transgender and gender non-conforming people, and address the issues the community faces.

text: i know there will be some events in portland around transgender day of remembrance on the 20th, which is set aside to honor lives lost to anti-transgender violence in the last year
including this event downtown on sunday: <https://www.facebook.com/events/1413747942257286/>

there’s lots of ways to participate though, from showing your support by donating to various organizations (like the Q center, or the ACLU) and to act as an ally by educating yourself around the various issues that trans* folks face in our community today
